<TITLE> SC hears Khoka bail challenge on July 24 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 13 (bdnews24.com)The Appellate Division on Sunday did not halt the High Court bail to Dhaka mayor Sadek Hossain Khoka in a graft case filed by the Anticorruption Commission. Appellate Division chamber judge Md Abdul Matin did not put freezes on the HC order that stayed the proceedings of the case in the trial court. The judge set July 24 for a hearing in the regular bench of the Appellate Division on the ACC's appeal to stay the HC order. Khurshid Alam Khan took part in the hearing of the appeal for a stay on the HC order on behalf of the ACC. Barrister Rafique-ul-Huq defended Khoka in court. Khoka who won bail from the HC in the case that involves the charges of earning wealth beyond his known income appeared before Dhaka metropolitan senior special judge's court Sunday and signed a Tk 20,000 bond for bail. The BNP leader's anticipatory bail will remain effective until July 16. Special court judge Azizul Haque who issued an arrest warrant against Khoka fixed July 17 to decide on the next step about the case. The ACC on April 2 filed the case against Khoka, his wife Ismat Ara, their daughter Sarika Sadeque and son Israq Hossain with Ramna Police Station on charges of earning wealth worth Tk 17.57 crore beyond his known income. bdnews24
